# cert-check service configuration
# Format: service_name  hostname[:port]  [proxy_ip:proxy_port]
#
# If proxy is specified, the connection goes to proxy_ip:proxy_port with SNI set to hostname.
# This is useful when all services are behind a reverse proxy (Traefik, Nginx, etc.)
#
# If no proxy is specified, the connection goes directly to hostname:443.

# --- Direct checks (no reverse proxy) ---
# google      google.com

# --- Via reverse proxy (all SNI through one IP) ---
# Common pattern: all services terminate TLS at the reverse proxy
# proxy_ip is your Traefik/Nginx/Caddy IP

# traefik       traefik.example.com       192.168.1.10:443
# forgejo       forgejo.example.com       192.168.1.10:443
# vaultwarden   vaultwarden.example.com   192.168.1.10:443
# homepage      homepage.example.com      192.168.1.10:443
# jellyfin      jellyfin.example.com      192.168.1.10:443
# immich        immich.example.com        192.168.1.10:443
